现在的重点是下周俄罗斯的峰会
We're focused on the summit next month with Russia.

345
00:16:13,470 --> 00:16:16,020
你还好吗  身体好起来了吗
But you're good? You getting stronger?

346
00:16:16,420 --> 00:16:18,480
-嗯  -精神呢
- Yeah. - In good spirits?

347
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:19,620
好得不得了
Never been better.

348
00:16:20,310 --> 00:16:22,540
我发邮件给你  他的想法记得告诉我
I'll email you my ideas. Let me know what he says.

349
00:16:23,130 --> 00:16:25,170
-没问题  -谢谢
- Will do. - Thanks.

350
00:16:28,940 --> 00:16:30,760
参议员  上周在办公室见面时
Senator, when we met in your office last week,

351
00:16:30,760 --> 00:16:32,560
我们进行了一次很长很有成果的谈话
we had a long, productive conversation.

352
00:16:32,570 --> 00:16:35,750
我觉得听证会上的十秒说明不...
I can't imagine ten seconds during the hearing would--

353
00:16:36,210 --> 00:16:38,950
参议员先生  我五分钟后再打过去好吗
Senator, may I call you back in five minutes?

354
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:40,220
谢谢
Thank you.

355
00:16:46,510 --> 00:16:49,610
-弗兰西斯  -不行  根本是他的主意
- Francis? - No luck. It was his idea.

356
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:52,100
你打算怎么做
What are you going to do?

357
00:16:52,980 --> 00:16:54,700
找上次竞选前50的资助人
Top 50 bundlers from last cycle.

358
00:16:54,700 --> 00:16:56,950
控制了资金我就不必靠领导层了
I don't need the leadership if I can get the money.

359
00:16:56,980 --> 00:16:58,350
-你呢  -还没准
- You? - Too early to tell.

360
00:16:58,350 --> 00:17:00,010
我就在这儿  需要就来找我
Well, I'm here if you need me.

361
00:17:03,580 --> 00:17:07,040
我一直说权力比金钱重要
I've always said that power is more important than money.

362
00:17:07,040 --> 00:17:10,380
但竞选的时候  金钱才能让权力
But when it comes to elections, money gives power...

363
00:17:10,900 --> 00:17:12,840
有竞争力
well, a run for its money.

364
00:17:14,210 --> 00:17:15,590
弗兰西斯·安德伍德
It's Francis Underwood.

365
00:17:25,290 --> 00:17:26,670
你说他挺帅的来着
I thought you said he was handsome.

366
00:17:28,010 --> 00:17:29,350
抱歉打扰了
Sorry to interrupt.

367
00:17:30,020 --> 00:17:33,110
如果她没收到说有"急事"的短信
Well, if she doesn't receive a text with the word "urgent,"

368
00:17:33,550 --> 00:17:34,850
那就算不上约会了
it's not an official date.

369
00:17:35,370 --> 00:17:36,840
你好  艾伦·库克
How are you? Alan Cooke.

370
00:17:36,900 --> 00:17:38,710
-雷米·丹顿  -幸会
- Remy Danton. - Nice to meet you.

371
00:17:39,720 --> 00:17:41,900
我去...打几个电话
I'm just gonna go, uh... take a few calls.

372
00:17:41,910 --> 00:17:44,700
我替你点了杯咖啡
There's an espresso coming with your name on it, okay?

373
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:45,640
再会
Nice meeting you.

374
00:17:51,630 --> 00:17:52,690
说说吧
So here we are.

375
00:17:53,390 --> 00:17:55,880
我没有参与  会面十分钟前他们才通知我
I wasn't part of the decision. They told me ten minutes before.

376
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:58,130
他们都找谁谈竞选的事了
Who are they talking to? About running?

377
00:17:58,130 --> 00:18:00,070
据我所知还没有
No one yet, as far as I can tell.

378
00:18:00,130 --> 00:18:03,160
总得有个名单  哪怕还没说出来
There has to at least be a list. Even a mental one.

379
00:18:03,350 --> 00:18:04,640
有些想法
Some ideas.

380
00:18:05,910 --> 00:18:07,410
我们需要你查出来
We need you to find out.

381
00:18:08,870 --> 00:18:10,860
沃克辞职的时候
You know, when Walker resigned,

382
00:18:11,340 --> 00:18:13,940
弗兰克就任总统  你是幕僚长
Frank's president, you're Chief of Staff.

383
00:18:13,940 --> 00:18:16,390
-我呢  -你还在领导层
- But me? - You're still in the leadership.

384
00:18:16,790 --> 00:18:19,260
-助理党鞭  -就是扯淡
- Assistant Whip. - It's a bullshit title.

385
00:18:19,760 --> 00:18:21,490
我不在核心圈子里
I'm out of the inner circle.

386
00:18:23,510 --> 00:18:24,620
那你要什么
What do you want?

387
00:18:26,120 --> 00:18:29,790
我要做他的副总统
I want to be on the ticket. His VP.

388
00:18:31,710 --> 00:18:33,220
我们只要一点点信息
All we want is a little information.

389
00:18:33,220 --> 00:18:37,300
你开的价  太高了吧
What you're asking is... disproportionate.

390
00:18:38,410 --> 00:18:40,570
当做是还债了吧
It's repaying a debt.

391
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:44,180
好大一笔债呢  弹劾法案是我搞定的
A big one. I whipped the votes for impeachment.

392
00:18:44,180 --> 00:18:46,110
现在我要回报了
I should get to cash in on that.

393
00:18:46,210 --> 00:18:48,130
他是不会同意的
There's no way he'll go for this.

394
00:18:48,390 --> 00:18:51,550
那我也没必要做你们的眼线了
Then there's no reason for me to be your eyes and ears.

395
00:18:55,350 --> 00:18:56,750
回头联系你
I'll get back to you.

396
00:18:58,060 --> 00:18:59,750
要在工作时间
During business hours.

397
00:19:18,250 --> 00:19:20,860
不  马克  就在白宫的决策室  我发誓
No, Mark, we ran it in the White House screening room and I swear to God,

398
00:19:20,860 --> 00:19:24,040
战斗机撞向海狼核潜艇的时候
when those jets crashed into one of our Seawolf subs,

399
00:19:24,040 --> 00:19:26,000
参联会都喊出来了
the Joint Chiefs screamed.

400
00:19:27,060 --> 00:19:29,280
他们肯定不希望你用  更不会免费给你
No, they didn't want you to use it and certainly not for free.

401
00:19:29,280 --> 00:19:30,930
大卫  我不只是要钱
David, I'm not just asking you for money,

402
00:19:30,930 --> 00:19:33,180
我希望你做我的竞选主席
I'm asking you to be one of my campaign chairmen.

403
00:19:33,190 --> 00:19:35,870
那可比在总统卧室睡一晚风光多了
That buys you a lot more than a night in the Lincoln Bedroom.

404
00:19:38,160 --> 00:19:40,040
克莱尔·安德伍德找海尔布鲁克参议员
Claire Underwood for Senator Hylbrook.

405
00:19:40,050 --> 00:19:43,140
我同意  肯定不能只靠安全委员会的支持
I agree. We can never rely solely upon Security Counsel support.

406
00:19:43,140 --> 00:19:44,550
斯科特  还剩18个月了
Scott, we're 18 months out.

407
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:45,950
你想参与进来
Now, if you wanna be on the ground floor,

408
00:19:45,950 --> 00:19:47,640
就别想占着茅坑不拉屎
you got to shit or get off the pot.

409
00:19:47,640 --> 00:19:51,220
关键是领导  做出榜样
The key is to provide leadership, to lead by example.

410
00:19:51,390 --> 00:19:54,380
我还想着一起去梅德斯通打打高尔夫呢
I was hoping we could hit Maidstone for a quick eighteen.

411
00:19:54,770 --> 00:19:56,610
当然不  我打得可差了
No, I'm a terrible golfer.

412
00:19:56,620 --> 00:19:59,000
是啊  你就可以打败总统了
Exactly, you'd have the pleasure of beating a president.

413
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:00,360
以后跟人可有得讲了
Now wouldn't that be a good cocktail story?

414
00:20:00,360 --> 00:20:03,480
我和您委员会里的共和党人差不多都谈过了
I've spoken to almost every Republican in your committee, sir.

415
00:20:04,320 --> 00:20:06,630
他们说都听您的
Yes, they're taking their cue from you.

416
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:11,370
还有别的号码可以联系上他吗
Is there another number where I can reach him?

417
00:20:11,370 --> 00:20:13,600
我今晚一定要跟他谈谈
It's important that we speak this evening.

418
00:20:15,320 --> 00:20:17,680
是的  不管多晚
Yes, anytime, no matter how late.

419
00:20:18,250 --> 00:20:20,600
汤姆  我只希望你多点信心
A little faith, Tom. That's all I'm asking.

420
00:20:20,600 --> 00:20:24,490
是啊  我也不喜欢别人叫我女士
Oh, yes! I know, I don't like being called "Ma'am" Either.

421
00:20:24,840 --> 00:20:27,120
要是我做什么事都得哄大伙开心
If I made every decision based on what makes people feel good,

422
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:29,190
那我就去主持脱口秀了  当什么总统
I'd be a talk show host, not the president.

423
00:20:29,200 --> 00:20:31,290
我知道詹宁斯上将是你的好朋友
Well, I know Admiral Jennings is a good friend of yours,

424
00:20:31,290 --> 00:20:33,740
-我可以亲自打给他  -别被恐惧左右
- I can call him personally. - Don't let fear drive you.

425
00:20:33,750 --> 00:20:35,080
你的生意不是这么做出来的吧
That's not how you run your business, is it?

426
00:20:35,090 --> 00:20:36,620
我知道你也曾被人曲解
I know you've been in my shoes,

427
00:20:36,620 --> 00:20:38,000
那种断章取义不是我们本意
and sound bites are not who we are.

428
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:39,230
那是省小钱吃大亏
Penny-wise and pound-foolish.

429
00:20:39,230 --> 00:20:41,720
抱歉  参议员  吵醒你了吗
I'm so sorry, Senator, did I wake you?

430
00:20:42,570 --> 00:20:44,730
好的  没事  我明天再挂
Yes, no, I'll try back again tomorrow.

431
00:20:44,730 --> 00:20:46,890
你目光短浅我不怪你
I can't fault you for being shortsighted.

432
00:20:46,900 --> 00:20:49,570
但我记性好你也别怪我
I hope you won't fault me for having a long memory.

433
00:20:49,580 --> 00:20:50,570
晚安
Good night!

434
00:20:54,740 --> 00:20:58,080
已经有人睡了  我明早再试
I'm waking people up now. I'll start again in the morning.

435
00:21:00,020 --> 00:21:03,250
-怎么样  -一点也说不准
- How's it looking? - I had to flip a coin? I don't know.

436
00:21:03,980 --> 00:21:06,900
-你呢  -还没人支持我
- You? - Not a single backer yet.

437
00:21:06,910 --> 00:21:08,910
-一个都没有吗  -加州那边还早
- Not one? - California's still awake.

438
00:21:08,920 --> 00:21:10,690
也许我在西海岸运气能好点
Maybe I'll have better luck out west.

439
00:21:10,690 --> 00:21:12,940
我出去跑一圈  我得做点什么
I'm going for a run. I need to do something.

440
00:21:12,940 --> 00:21:14,770
-太晚了  -我闲不下来了
- It's late. - Well, I'm too restless.

441
00:21:14,770 --> 00:21:18,190
那我一个人在这儿吃晚饭了
Well, I'll be here, singing for my supper.

442
00:21:24,370 --> 00:21:27,240
求个脸书上的毛头小子
It's humiliating to have to beg from some kid who was on Facebook

443
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:29,630
实在丢人  但那是...
before his testicles descended, but that's--

444
00:21:29,770 --> 00:21:32,840
德里克  弗兰西斯·安德伍德  有时间吗
Derrick, Francis Underwood. Do you have a few minutes?

445
00:21:34,930 --> 00:21:36,620
我绕着国家广场跑
I'll be running along the Mall tonight.

446
00:21:36,620 --> 00:21:38,360
那要出动全套安保
That requires a full detail.

447
00:21:38,830 --> 00:21:40,330
你们多久能准备好
How soon can you be ready?

448
00:21:40,330 --> 00:21:42,570
我们更希望您在附近跑
We'd far prefer you ran on the track.

449
00:21:42,750 --> 00:21:44,230
我去国家广场跑
I'll be running along the Mall.

450
00:21:44,230 --> 00:21:48,400
好的  夫人  第一夫人安保尽快出动
Yes, ma'am. We're going to need the First Lady's detail, ASAP.

451
00:21:51,170 --> 00:21:53,320
-不可公开  -可以
- This is off the record. - Agreed.

452
00:21:54,580 --> 00:21:56,390
过去六个月
You've called my office every day

453
00:21:56,390 --> 00:21:58,650
你一直给我办公室打电话  问同一个问题
for the last six months with one question.

454
00:21:58,650 --> 00:22:00,690
领导层的人我都联系过
I call everyone in the leadership.

455
00:22:00,780 --> 00:22:02,930
得到的都是同一套说辞
I get the same non-answer from all of you:

456
00:22:02,930 --> 00:22:04,750
"弗兰克·安德伍德是现任总统"
"Frank Underwood is our president..."

457
00:22:04,750 --> 00:22:07,060
我们是他坚实的后盾
He has our undivided support.

458
00:22:07,060 --> 00:22:07,970
博奇有次说错了
Birch slipped up once.

459
00:22:07,970 --> 00:22:10,810
他说"不可动摇"不是"坚实"
He said "unwavering" instead of "undivided."

460
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,650
我还以为他嗑药了
I wanted to drug-test him.

461
00:22:12,860 --> 00:22:15,220
今早在白宫有过一次会面
There was a meeting this morning in the White House.

462
00:22:16,040 --> 00:22:17,710
你们出来时我看到了
I was there on Pebble Beach when you came out.

463
00:22:17,880 --> 00:22:20,090
一共就谈了四分半
It lasted four and a half minutes.

464
00:22:20,100 --> 00:22:23,150
-你们进去了一个小时  -是待了一个小时
- You were in there for an hour. - We were inside for an hour.

465
00:22:23,150 --> 00:22:25,210
但不代表就谈了一个小时
Doesn't mean the meeting lasted that long.

466
00:22:25,750 --> 00:22:27,310
发生什么了  为什么这么快
What happened? Why so short?

467
00:22:30,880 --> 00:22:32,740
你入围过普利策奖呢
You're the Pulitzer finalist.

468
00:22:32,790 --> 00:22:34,000
《美国就业法案》吗
America Works?

469
00:22:35,530 --> 00:22:37,870
总统下午是为了这个去的国会山吗
Is that why the president went to the Capitol this afternoon?

470
00:22:37,870 --> 00:22:39,660
白宫的人都不松口
No one from the White House would say.

471
00:22:44,750 --> 00:22:46,030
晚安
Have a good night.

472
00:22:49,130 --> 00:22:51,500
你选了我  你想干什么
You chose me. What's your play?

473
00:22:51,650 --> 00:22:54,310
只要是写总统的  人们都会关注
When you write about presidents, people pay attention.

474
00:25:09,180 --> 00:25:10,770
得最后定胜负了
It'll come down to the wire.

475
00:25:11,510 --> 00:25:14,340
我有信心  但我也不希望有什么事听天由命
I'm confident, but I don't want to leave anything to chance.

476
00:25:15,640 --> 00:25:19,920
据艾瑞克森的消息  我今早有47票了
Well, according to Erikson, I have 47 votes as of this morning.

477
00:25:21,290 --> 00:25:22,940
我知道  参议员  但那还不够
Well, I know, Senator, but that's not enough.

478
00:25:22,940 --> 00:25:24,420
我还需要您的票
I need yours.

479
00:25:34,740 --> 00:25:38,330
我绝对是要竞选总统的
I have every intention of running for president.

480
00:25:38,690 --> 00:25:40,540
我得确定你们是支持我的
I need to know you two are with me.

481
00:25:40,540 --> 00:25:43,460
有任何疑虑  就现在说出来
If you have any doubts, now's the time to let me know.

482
00:25:51,620 --> 00:25:54,060
南茜  清空时间表
Nancy, wipe the schedule clean.

483
00:25:54,220 --> 00:25:55,420
全推掉
Yes, everything.

484
00:25:56,030 --> 00:25:58,130
不讨论出个计划就不出去
We don't leave this office until we have a plan.

485
00:26:00,900 --> 00:26:04,090
夫人  复活节滚彩蛋游戏的事
Ma'am? The Easter Egg Roll we were scheduled for?

486
00:26:04,090 --> 00:26:05,770
-是啊  -如果不方便...
- Right. - If this is a bad time...

487
00:26:05,770 --> 00:26:07,860
没什么  进来吧
No, that's fine. Please, come in.

488
00:26:08,900 --> 00:26:09,700
你好
Hello?

489
00:26:09,700 --> 00:26:12,530
是的  克莱尔·安德伍德  他在等我电话
Yes... Claire Underwood. He's expecting my call.

490
00:26:14,290 --> 00:26:16,080
你好  希拉  真美
Hi, Sheila. They're beautiful.

491
00:26:16,080 --> 00:26:17,240
摆一下好吗
Would you mind setting them up, please?

492
00:26:17,240 --> 00:26:19,300
我还要打几个电话
I have a couple more calls to make.

493
00:26:19,530 --> 00:26:24,110
参议员  我挺好  您好吗
Hello, Senator. Yes, I'm well. How are you?

494
00:26:25,730 --> 00:26:28,650
提名华盛顿特区克莱尔·安德伍德
The nomination of Claire Underwood, of Washington DC,

495
00:26:28,650 --> 00:26:29,930
担任美利坚合众国
to be the Representative of

496
00:26:29,940 --> 00:26:32,900
驻联合国代表
the United States of America to the United Nations.

497
00:26:32,900 --> 00:26:36,370
请听书记官喊名字  投赞成和反对
Yeas and nays have been ordered and the clerk will call the roll.

498
00:26:37,130 --> 00:26:38,840
-阿博纳先生  -赞成
- Mr. Abner. - Yea.

499
00:26:39,760 --> 00:26:40,800
博朗先生
Mr. Braun.

500
00:26:42,310 --> 00:26:43,390
布雷先生
Mr. Bray.

501
00:26:44,760 --> 00:26:48,200
-这个太粉了  -小姑娘都喜欢粉色
- This one's a little too pink. - Girls like pink.

502
00:26:48,350 --> 00:26:50,410
这可不止是粉色了  几乎是霓虹色了
This is more than pink. It's neon.

503
00:26:51,220 --> 00:26:53,270
-我要选四个吗  -是的  夫人
- Uh, I'm choosing four? - Yes, ma'am.

504
00:26:53,340 --> 00:26:56,150
-薇拉  -领先两票  48对46
- Willa? - Up by two: 48 to 46.

505
00:26:56,150 --> 00:26:58,290
-夫人  我们可以稍后再做  -不用
- Ma'am, we can finish up later. - No.

506
00:26:58,290 --> 00:27:00,600
-下面呢  -纪念彩蛋
- Uh, what's next? - The commemoratives.

507
00:27:00,600 --> 00:27:02,210
都很特别
These are really special.

508
00:27:02,690 --> 00:27:03,860
黑蛋吗
A black egg?

509
00:27:03,860 --> 00:27:07,160
-有爱国元素点缀  -那也是黑蛋
- Yes, with patriotic tipping. - It's still a black egg.

510
00:27:07,160 --> 00:27:09,140
刻着美国总统与第一夫人的签名
Engraved with POTUS and FLOTUS signatures.

