00:27:12,600 --> 00:27:13,680
反对占多
Against.

513
00:27:20,820 --> 00:27:23,070
-媒体呢  -在通气室
- The press? - In the briefing room.

514
00:27:25,220 --> 00:27:27,780
我就回来  稍等一下好吗
I'll just be a few minutes. Would you mind waiting?

515
00:27:27,780 --> 00:27:28,880
当然  夫人
Not at all, ma'am.

516
00:27:41,890 --> 00:27:43,250
我听说了
I just heard.

517
00:27:44,580 --> 00:27:46,210
真遗憾
I'm so sorry.

518
00:27:47,090 --> 00:27:47,990
媒体等着呢
The press is waiting.

519
00:27:47,990 --> 00:27:49,500
他们等去吧
Well, they can wait.

520
00:27:50,020 --> 00:27:50,920
要我陪你去吗
Do you want me to come with you?

521
00:27:50,920 --> 00:27:53,140
不用  我就想尽快了事
No. I just want to get it over with.

522
00:27:55,540 --> 00:27:57,810
克莱尔  你...
Claire. You--

523
00:28:06,620 --> 00:28:07,670
早上好
Good morning.

524
00:28:07,840 --> 00:28:10,340
参议院没有通过我的提名  
Naturally, I'm disappointed

525
00:28:10,340 --> 00:28:13,600
我自然很失望
that the Senate did not confirm my nomination today.

526
00:28:14,020 --> 00:28:17,340
但能得到这个机会  我已经很感激
But I'm very grateful to have been afforded the opportunity.

527
00:28:17,790 --> 00:28:20,090
我自然要谢谢我的丈夫
I'd be remiss if I did not thank my husband

528
00:28:20,090 --> 00:28:22,560
感谢他对我的支持与信任
for all the faith and trust he placed in me.

529
00:28:23,240 --> 00:28:25,950
他一向支持我实现梦想
He's always supported me in achieving my goals.

530
00:28:26,850 --> 00:28:31,070
我期待继续履行第一夫人的职责
I look forward to continued service as First Lady.

531
00:28:31,550 --> 00:28:32,470
谢谢
Thank you.

532
00:28:47,840 --> 00:28:51,820
选绿的  蓝的  和米色的吧
Um, let's go with the... green, the blue, and the cream.

533
00:28:51,820 --> 00:28:54,900
纪念彩蛋呢  可以说是金券
And for the rare one? The Golden Ticket, so to speak?

534
00:28:55,880 --> 00:28:58,210
红的  红的好看
Red. That one's beautiful.

535
00:28:58,750 --> 00:29:01,280
谢谢  我先走了
Thank you. Excuse me, please?

536
00:29:25,030 --> 00:29:26,480
你试过吗
You ever try to do this?

537
00:29:28,260 --> 00:29:29,520
让蛋立住
Balance an egg?

538
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:33,700
我们小时候常玩
We used to do this as kids.

539
00:29:42,860 --> 00:29:45,770
物理法则是没法改的吧
You can't change the laws of physics, can you?

540
00:29:59,280 --> 00:30:02,590
我错了  太难了
I was wrong. It's too hard.

541
00:30:02,620 --> 00:30:03,370
先生
Sir?

542
00:30:03,560 --> 00:30:06,520
对抗领导层  筹集竞选资金
Fighting the leadership, raising money.

543
00:30:06,790 --> 00:30:08,840
不能强迫他们做极不情愿的事
We can't get them to do what they're dead set against doing.

544
00:30:08,840 --> 00:30:11,950
现在是负分  要拉到零都需要六个月
We'd need six months just to get them back to square one.

545
00:30:22,880 --> 00:30:25,210
得逆向思维
We have to reverse our thinking.

546
00:30:29,310 --> 00:30:31,620
当强风袭来的时候
When the wind's blowing at gale force,

547
00:30:31,620 --> 00:30:33,990
没有必要逆风航行
there's no point in sailing against it.

548
00:30:36,780 --> 00:30:38,000
您有什么主意
What do you have in mind?

549
00:31:07,840 --> 00:31:09,910
请接白宫法律顾问办公室
The White House Counsel's office, please.

550
00:31:09,910 --> 00:31:11,270
我不管他们有什么安排
I don't care about their schedules.

551
00:31:11,270 --> 00:31:12,620
今天凑不齐那就明天早上
If not today, tomorrow morning.

552
00:31:12,620 --> 00:31:13,850
我们还请杰姬来吗
Should I invite Jackie, too?

553
00:31:13,850 --> 00:31:15,750
她毕竟还算是领导层里的
Well, she qualifies as leadership.

554
00:31:15,750 --> 00:31:17,860
-那她的条件呢  -先拖着
- What about her ask? - Stall her for now.

555
00:31:17,860 --> 00:31:19,610
看看会面怎样再说
Let's see how the meeting goes.

556
00:31:20,070 --> 00:31:22,110
你给我写份讲稿  要字斟句酌
I want you to write the speech, every word.

557
00:31:22,120 --> 00:31:23,700
-好的  先生  -不得外泄
- Yes, sir. - And no leaks.

558
00:31:23,700 --> 00:31:25,680
三小时内给您草稿
You'll have a draft in three hours.

559
00:31:26,370 --> 00:31:30,400
另外  道格给我发了份《美就法》的游说策略
And, sir... Doug emailed me a lobbying strategy for AmWorks.

560
00:31:30,400 --> 00:31:32,270
-您要看一看吗  -他自己写的吗
- Do you want to look at it? - Of his own accord?

561
00:31:32,270 --> 00:31:34,100
-你没告诉他吧  -我什么都没说
- You didn't tell him? - No, I didn't say a word.

562
00:31:34,100 --> 00:31:36,070
肯定是他看新闻自己琢磨出来的
It must be what he gathered from watching the news.

563
00:31:36,070 --> 00:31:39,220
-他怎样了  -道格听起来还行
- How is he? - Uh, Doug seems fine.

564
00:31:39,220 --> 00:31:40,940
按您的要求  我一直在给他打电话
I've been calling him, like you asked.

565
00:31:41,410 --> 00:31:43,420
-但他看起来如何  -他告诉我一切都好
- But he seems all right? - Well, he tells me things are good,

566
00:31:43,430 --> 00:31:45,830
不过我估计就算不好他也不会说的
although I don't think he'd admit it if they weren't.

567
00:31:46,830 --> 00:31:49,120
不如你抽空去看看他  我抽不出身
Why don't you stop by from time to time, since I can't.

568
00:31:49,120 --> 00:31:50,630
-要亲眼见到他  -好的  先生
- See him in person. - Yes, sir.

569
00:31:50,630 --> 00:31:51,820
把他的策略转给我
And send me his email.

570
00:32:02,790 --> 00:32:03,710
克莱尔
Claire?

571
00:32:08,360 --> 00:32:10,400
如果你找我  我就在书房
I'll be in my study if you need me.

572
00:32:16,670 --> 00:32:17,670
你忙什么呢
What're you working on?

573
00:32:19,280 --> 00:32:21,800
-给你带了杯咖啡  -你可救了我的命了
- Brought you a coffee. - My savior.

574
00:32:22,110 --> 00:32:24,060
党领导层昨天开了个会
The leadership meeting yesterday morning.

575
00:32:24,070 --> 00:32:25,930
只持续了四分半
It lasted four and a half minutes.

576
00:32:26,300 --> 00:32:27,180
你从哪听说的
Where'd you hear that?

577
00:32:27,180 --> 00:32:29,820
这么重大的内政议题不可能这么快就否了
That's not long enough to reject a major domestic agenda.

578
00:32:30,700 --> 00:32:32,980
我又没出席  我怎么知道会开了多久
I wasn't in the meeting. I don't know how long it lasted.

579
00:32:33,230 --> 00:32:35,830
-出了什么事  -随你怎么说了
- Something went down. - If you say so.

580
00:32:36,230 --> 00:32:37,800
反正我是什么都没听说
Uh, I didn't hear anything about it.

581
00:32:38,660 --> 00:32:40,640
没准是总统有急事先走了
Could've been the president was called away.

582
00:32:40,650 --> 00:32:43,560
-经常这样  -这次不是
- That happens all the time. - Not this time.

583
00:32:44,020 --> 00:32:44,930
你怎么知道
How do you know?

584
00:32:45,480 --> 00:32:47,740
显然我有个知道的比你多的消息源
Clearly, I have a source that knows more than you.

585
00:32:48,530 --> 00:32:51,620
大多数消息源都这样  至少是假装这样
Most sources do. At least they pretend they do.

586
00:32:53,050 --> 00:32:54,180
多谢你的咖啡
Thanks for the coffee.

587
00:32:56,010 --> 00:32:58,850
加两包糖  我下次会记得的
Two sugars next time. I'll remember that.

588
00:33:06,550 --> 00:33:07,990
你和艾拉·萨伊德谈过了
You talked to Ayla Sayyad.

589
00:33:07,990 --> 00:33:10,770
我既可以帮忙也可以帮倒忙
I can either be an asset or a liability.

590
00:33:11,340 --> 00:33:12,760
你以为这样就能保你成为竞选搭档了吗
You think this puts you on the ticket now?

591
00:33:12,760 --> 00:33:14,140
你去告密的话自然不会了
Not if you tell him.

592
00:33:14,230 --> 00:33:16,660
不过比较聪明的选择是替我说好话
But the smart move would be to advocate on my behalf.

593
00:33:16,660 --> 00:33:17,920
别逼我  杰姬
Don't strong-arm me, Jackie.

594
00:33:17,930 --> 00:33:20,490
你是中间人  不逼你逼谁
You're the man in the middle. Who else would I strong-arm?

595
00:33:20,520 --> 00:33:22,420
我想成为你们的一员  雷米
I want to be on your team, Remy.

596
00:33:22,790 --> 00:33:24,720
我们合作的时候结果一向不错
We do well when we're on the same team.

597
00:33:29,210 --> 00:33:30,420
你还有别的电话吗
You have more calls?

598
00:33:31,600 --> 00:33:34,510
没有  忙完了
No. I'm done.

599
00:33:36,390 --> 00:33:38,770
-谁向她泄密了  -我不知道  先生
- Who spoke to her? - I have no idea, sir.

600
00:33:38,770 --> 00:33:41,480
-你的工作就是知道  -事情发展太快
- Well, it's your job to know. - Things are moving fast.

601
00:33:41,480 --> 00:33:42,720
我只想尽力控制局面
I'm just trying to stay ahead of them.

602
00:33:42,720 --> 00:33:45,160
我们动作得再快点  会面定下来了吗
Well, we need to move faster. Has the meeting been set?

603
00:33:45,160 --> 00:33:47,790
明早8点  博奇的办公室刚给我回了话
Eight AM tomorrow. I just heard back from Birch's office.

604
00:33:47,790 --> 00:33:50,020
很好  联系媒体准备好9点直播
Good. Let's have the networks ready to go live by nine.

605
00:33:50,020 --> 00:33:52,440
还有个问题  杰姬
One more thing. Jackie.

606
00:33:53,180 --> 00:33:55,100
我觉得你最好尽快做决定
I think you should decide sooner rather than later.

607
00:33:55,100 --> 00:33:55,970
如果我们走这条路
If we're gonna go this route,

608
00:33:55,970 --> 00:33:57,140
就得争取尽可能多的友军
we need every ally we can get.

609
00:33:57,150 --> 00:33:59,110
等开完会  我们再谈
After the meeting. We'll discuss then.

610
00:34:12,360 --> 00:34:13,860
你起来了啊
You've emerged.

611
00:34:17,450 --> 00:34:20,970
我小睡了一觉  昨晚我都没怎么睡
I took a nap. Last night was... I didn't get much sleep.

612
00:34:21,510 --> 00:34:22,500
我也是
Me, neither.

613
00:34:24,060 --> 00:34:25,810
我们肯定会给你找个职位的
We're gonna find something for you.

614
00:34:25,860 --> 00:34:30,080
其它的职位  或作为第一夫人的职责  我保证
Some other position, or something as First Lady, I promise.

615
00:34:30,930 --> 00:34:31,860
我知道
I know.

616
00:34:33,480 --> 00:34:35,670
-你不睡做什么  -我在忙我的演说
- What are you doing up? - I've got to go over my speech.

617
00:34:35,670 --> 00:34:37,850
我准备明晚发表演讲
It's happening tomorrow night.

618
00:34:37,900 --> 00:34:39,170
什么演讲
What speech?

619
00:34:51,510 --> 00:34:53,040
有点太急了  不是吗
It's premature, isn't it?

620
00:34:53,140 --> 00:34:54,070
读下去
Read on.

621
00:35:38,140 --> 00:35:39,050
好吗
Yes?

622
00:35:41,350 --> 00:35:42,280
好
Yes.

623
00:35:47,360 --> 00:35:48,630
谢谢  请坐
Thank you. Please.

624
00:35:54,860 --> 00:35:58,160
你们的请求  我想了很多
I put a great deal of thought into what you've all asked of me.

625
00:35:58,670 --> 00:36:01,260
我让自己尽量保持开放的态度
I challenged myself to keep an open mind.

626
00:36:01,850 --> 00:36:05,940
而我的决定是  我将不参选下任总统
And my decision is: I will not run for president.

627
00:36:06,840 --> 00:36:09,760
他们觉得这好的不真实  也的确不是真的
Look, they're thinking it's too good to be true, and it is.

628
00:36:09,760 --> 00:36:11,450
我之前在椭圆办公室撒过谎
I lied in the Oval Office before.

629
00:36:11,450 --> 00:36:13,100
这次不想再触霉头
I didn't want to take the chance this time.

630
00:36:13,100 --> 00:36:15,280
万一真说中了可不好
It's too big a deal to jinx myself.

631
00:36:15,740 --> 00:36:16,810
今晚9点
At nine o'clock tonight,

632
00:36:16,810 --> 00:36:19,320
我就向全国宣布我的决定
I will announce to the nation my decision.

633
00:36:19,320 --> 00:36:20,820
你什么目的
What's the catch?

634
00:36:22,400 --> 00:36:26,490
我要大家来这里见面是有原因的
I wanted us to meet here in this room for a reason.

635
00:36:26,860 --> 00:36:27,990
过去五个月
For the past five months,

636
00:36:27,990 --> 00:36:31,830
我的团队就坐在这儿  起草《美国就业法案》
my team has sat at this very table, developing America Works.

637
00:36:31,830 --> 00:36:34,020
你们知道这项目对我意义重大
You know how much the program means to me,

638
00:36:34,020 --> 00:36:35,550
我希望你们也能像我一样重视
and I want it to mean as much to you.

639
00:36:35,560 --> 00:36:38,740
-那你是有目的的了  -不  是机遇
- So there is a catch. - No, an opportunity.

640
00:36:38,740 --> 00:36:40,190
我们都知道
Look, we all know the--

641
00:36:41,990 --> 00:36:44,330
单纯地打个比方
All right, let's just say for... argument's sake

642
00:36:44,330 --> 00:36:45,550
这张桌子
that this table here

643
00:36:45,550 --> 00:36:48,330
就是未来一年半
represents the next year and a half, all right?

644
00:36:48,330 --> 00:36:50,430
我们在这儿
So, this is us right now.

645
00:36:50,430 --> 00:36:52,600
那边的尽头是大选
And down there at the end, that's the election.

646
00:36:52,610 --> 00:36:56,920
我要是决定竞选  接下来几个月我就得筹款
Now, if I did run, I'd spend the next few months fundraising.

647
00:36:56,920 --> 00:36:59,850
到这时左右  我要正式宣布
And then somewhere around here, I'd formally announce.

648
00:36:59,850 --> 00:37:01,680
哪怕我赢了党内竞选
And then even if I did win the nomination,

649
00:37:01,680 --> 00:37:03,370
比如说在这个时候
say, somewhere around here,

650
00:37:03,370 --> 00:37:04,970
我就得面对
I'd start to have to face off

651
00:37:04,970 --> 00:37:07,270
共和党的对手  很可能是门多萨
with a Republican challenger, probably Mendoza.

652
00:37:07,270 --> 00:37:09,580
那可就是真刀真枪了
And then things would get brutal.

653
00:37:09,940 --> 00:37:11,730
每天都得去做活动
Daily, daily events.

654
00:37:11,800 --> 00:37:13,510
防御对手的进攻
Fending off attacks.

655
00:37:13,510 --> 00:37:15,180
同时进攻对手
Launching my own.

656
00:37:15,210 --> 00:37:18,000
你们说得对
And... you're right.

657
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:19,180
最后...
In the end...

658
00:37:19,870 --> 00:37:21,610
...我可能会输
...I'd probably lose.

659
00:37:22,510 --> 00:37:26,200
我会花18个月的时间竞选
I would spend 18 months campaigning,

660
00:37:26,470 --> 00:37:29,720
就没有时间治国了
which would leave no time to govern.

661
00:37:31,610 --> 00:37:34,630
你们让我看清了局势
But you have opened my eyes.

662
00:37:34,830 --> 00:37:36,680
解放了思想
I feel liberated.

663
00:37:36,680 --> 00:37:41,310
接下来的18个月我想专注一件事
I want to spend these next 18 months dedicated to one thing:

664
00:37:41,310 --> 00:37:44,390
《美国就业法案》  但我需要你们的帮助
America Works. But I need your help to do it.

665
00:37:44,390 --> 00:37:47,160
你开的价码有点高啊  总统先生
You're putting an awfully big price tag on this, Mr. President.

666
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:49,730
不  是你们开了高额价码
No, you've put an awfully big price tag on this.

667
00:37:49,730 --> 00:37:52,420
你们要我占18个月的位子
You're asking me to be a placeholder for 18 months

668
00:37:52,420 --> 00:37:54,240
而我想治国
and I intend to govern.

669
00:37:54,650 --> 00:37:56,510
如果《美国就业法案》成功了
And if America Works succeeds,

670
00:37:56,520 --> 00:37:59,060
那不管16年谁来竞选
then whoever you choose to run in 2016

671
00:37:59,060 --> 00:38:01,750
都会有全党的支持
not only has the backing of a united party,

672
00:38:01,950 --> 00:38:03,610
更会有一笔可贵的遗产
but a formidable legacy.

673
00:38:03,610 --> 00:38:07,290
社会保障呢  社会福利呢
But Social Security? Benefits. Entitlements.

674
00:38:07,290 --> 00:38:08,890
我们可不想推选个新人
We don't want to present a fresh face

675
00:38:08,890 --> 00:38:10,450
反过来坑了自己
only to shoot ourselves in the foot.

676
00:38:10,450 --> 00:38:13,130
那就别假装全党统一了
Then let's not pretend to unite the party,

677
00:38:13,130 --> 00:38:15,830
让全党统一支持这项法案吧
let's unite the party behind this legislation.

678
00:38:15,830 --> 00:38:17,460
肯定过不了共和党那关
We'll never get it past the Republicans.

679
00:38:17,460 --> 00:38:19,720
我们不是来谈判的
We are not here to negotiate!

680
00:38:19,730 --> 00:38:22,810
你要放眼未来吗  鲍勃  快放眼看啊
You want forward-thinking, Bob? Then think forward.

681
00:38:22,810 --> 00:38:26,440
想16年推举个新人吗  想通力合作吗
You want a fresh face for 2016? You wanna work together?

682
00:38:26,440 --> 00:38:28,680
把我的法案递交给国会吧
Then present my program to Congress.

683
00:38:28,680 --> 00:38:30,910
如果通不过  那也没办法
And if it dies there, so be it.

684
00:38:30,910 --> 00:38:34,830
但我们至少他妈该试一下
But I want us to fucking try!

685
00:38:43,400 --> 00:38:45,890
我打算让位了
I am prepared to vacate this chair.

686
00:38:46,860 --> 00:38:48,310
你们也妥协一下
Meet me halfway.

687
00:38:49,220 --> 00:38:50,020
很快
Any moment now,

